The paper discusses the concept of social autonomous agents for collision avoidance in autonomous vehicles, which involves interaction and prediction of intentions. This falls under the category of multi-agent systems and robotics, making cs.MA and cs.RO the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of exploratory agent-based modeling and a mathematical model, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of the proposed scheme, which could also fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
